@startuml
title Library Management System - Combined Sequence Flows

actor "Student/User" as Student
participant "Web UI" as UI
participant "Catalog Service" as Catalog
participant "Reservation Service" as Reservation
actor "Librarian/Admin" as Librarian
participant "Loan Service" as Loan
database "Inventory DB" as DB
participant "Report Service" as Report

== Book Reservation and Issue Flow ==

Student -> UI : Search book by title / author
UI -> Catalog : findAvailableBooks(criteria)
Catalog -> DB : checkAvailability(bookId / filters)
DB --> Catalog : available copies and status
Catalog --> UI : matching books with availability

Student -> UI : Select book and reserve
UI -> Reservation : createReservation(studentId, bookId)
Reservation -> DB : holdAvailableCopy(bookId)
DB --> Reservation : copy held / reservation pending
Reservation --> UI : reservation submitted

UI -> Librarian : notify reservation request
Librarian --> UI : approve request

UI -> Loan : issueBook(reservationId)
Loan -> DB : markCopyAsIssued(copyId)
DB --> Loan : status updated = Issued
Loan --> UI : loan created with due date

UI --> Student : issue confirmation and due date

== Book Return, Overdue Check, and Report Flow ==

Student -> Librarian : Return borrowed book
Librarian -> UI : Scan barcode / select loan
UI -> Loan : getLoanDetails(copyId)
Loan --> UI : active loan and due date

Librarian -> UI : confirm return
UI -> Loan : returnBook(loanId, returnDate)
Loan -> DB : markCopyAsAvailable(copyId)
DB --> Loan : status updated = Available
Loan --> UI : return processed / fine status

UI --> Student : return confirmation

Librarian -> UI : request overdue report
UI -> Report : generateOverdueReport()
Report -> Loan : fetchActiveOverdueLoans()
Loan --> Report : overdue loan list
Report --> UI : compiled overdue report

UI --> Librarian : display / export report
@enduml
